'''Museum board''' is a special type of cardboard.  Specifically, it is a white, acid free cardboard with  the interesting property that it flexes fairly easily in one direction but it is fairly stiff in the other.  This is because of the [[Bookbinding/Grain|grain]] of the paper fibers.  Denny Jones recommends two ply museum board for [[Bookbinding/Long stitch|long stitch]] binding. Good art-supply stores carry this.  One sheet will make about eight book covers for books printed on standard sized typing paper.

